<subSubSection id="C34E0491FFE7FFF388844616CC03FDEC" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEB571AFFE7FFF388844616CC03FDEC" blockId="12.[151,1127,289,634]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF388844616CC59FEAF" bold="true" box="[151,271,289,313]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Comment.</emphasis>
In book on animal life of the 
<collectingCountry id="F343178AFFE7FFF38A534615CFC7FEAC" box="[576,657,290,314]" name="Yemen" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Socotra</collectingCountry>
Archipelago 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC52AEBFFE7FFF38B0E4615CEE8FEAC" author="WRANIK W." box="[797,958,290,314]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" refId="ref5073" refString="WRANIK W. 2003: Fauna of the Socotra Archipelago. Field Guide. Universitatsdruckerei Rostock, 542 pp." type="book" year="2003">WRANIK (2003)</bibRefCitation>
showed a photo of a cassidine beetle identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C542C99FFE7FFF389EF4674CFB2FECC" baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[508,740,323,346]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxylepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deflexicollis">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF389EF4674CFB2FECC" box="[508,740,323,346]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Oxylepus deflexicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although we had no opportunity to study the specimen, in our opinion it was misidentified. In this area the only species of this genus occurs – 
<taxonomicName id="4C542C99FFE7FFF3892C46B4CCE8FE0C" authorityName=": SPAETH" authorityYear="1914" box="[319,446,387,410]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxylepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kossmati">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF3892C46B4CCE8FE0C" box="[319,446,387,410]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">O. kossmati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was recorded from 
<collectingRegion id="499099F8FFE7FFF38AA746B5CFA6FE0C" box="[692,752,386,410]" country="Yemen" name="'Adan" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Aden</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F343178AFFE7FFF38AEF46B5CE16FE0C" box="[764,832,386,410]" name="Oman" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Oman</collectingCountry>
, Erythrea, Djibuti, 
<collectingCountry id="F343178AFFE7FFF38C1C46B5C930FE0C" box="[1039,1126,386,410]" name="Somalia" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Somalia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F343178AFFE7FFF388D74695CC72FE2C" box="[196,292,418,442]" name="Tanzania" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC52AEBFFE7FFF389204695CC88FE2C" author="BOROWIEC L." box="[307,478,418,442]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" refId="ref4431" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2002: A monograph of the Afrotropical Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Part III. Revision of the tribe Cassidini 1, except the genera Aethiopocassis Sp., Cassida L., and Chiridopsis Sp. Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 292 pp + 17 pls." type="book" year="2002">BOROWIEC 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The species was described based on maculate form, thus in key to the Palearctic Cassidinae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC52AEBFFE7FFF389E946F5CFA0FE4F" author="SPAETH F. &amp; REITTER E." box="[506,758,449,474]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" refId="ref4921" refString="SPAETH F. &amp; REITTER E. 1926: Bestimmungs-Tabellen der europaischen Coleopteren. 95 Heft. Cassidinae der palaearktischen Region. E. Reitter, Troppau, 68 pp." type="book" year="1926">SPAETH &amp; REITTER 1926</bibRefCitation>
) the main distinguishing character of 
<taxonomicName id="4C542C99FFE7FFF388A646D4CC62FE6C" authorityName=": SPAETH" authorityYear="1914" box="[181,308,483,506]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxylepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kossmati">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF388A646D4CC62FE6C" box="[181,308,483,506]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">O. kossmati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from other species was maculate elytra. Recent material showed that it is a variable species and forms both maculate and immaculate morphs; thus immaculate specimens can be misidentified with very similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C542C99FFE7FFF38A644514CE44FDAC" box="[631,786,547,570]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxylepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delexicollis">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF38A644514CE44FDAC" box="[631,786,547,570]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">O. delexicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which differs only in distinctly shorter scutellum. Detailed redescription of 
<taxonomicName id="4C542C99FFE7FFF38A614574CFA7FDCC" authorityName=": SPAETH" authorityYear="1914" box="[626,753,579,602]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Oxylepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kossmati">
<emphasis id="B9208B08FFE7FFF38A614574CFA7FDCC" box="[626,753,579,602]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">O. kossmati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and colour photos are available in 
